
                                            Lusanda Ntantiso was arrested after a 20-minute car chase that started in Marele Street.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Police in the Eastern Cape have arrested a 30-year-old man for house robberies dating back to 2015. Authorities spotted Lusanda Ntantiso in Kwazakhele. After a 20-minute car chase that started in Marele Street, police apprehended Ntantiso where he was charged with at least two counts of house robberies. Ntantiso is expected to appear in the Motherwell Magistrates Court on 17 November.  Police spokesperson Andre Beetge said: “After tailing the suspect, he started speeding off… skipping red traffic lights and bumping into other vehicles on the road in an attempt to escape.”